<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="358" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,583,753]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">
The females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang &amp; Yin" authorityYear="1992" box="[323,412,583,609]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Tonsilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[323,412,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">Tonsilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily recognized by the large epigynal atrium, epigynal teeth situated anteriorly, and the large copulatory ducts, while the males can be recognized by the long patellar apophysis, a short cymbial furrow, and the bifurcate (or lobed) conductor. Chelicerae of both sexes with three promarginal and two retromarginal teeth (
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, X. P." box="[159,301,691,717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref8867" refString="Wang, X. P. (2002) A generic-level revision of the spider subfamily Coelotinae (Araneae, Amaurobiidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 269, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2002) 269 % 3 C 0001: AGLROT % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2002">Wang, 2002</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, X. P." box="[319,466,691,717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref8867" refString="Wang, X. P. (2002) A generic-level revision of the spider subfamily Coelotinae (Araneae, Amaurobiidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 269, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2002) 269 % 3 C 0001: AGLROT % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2002">Wang (2002)</bibRefCitation>
considered this genus as the sister group of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kishida, 1955" authorityName="Kishida" authorityYear="1955" box="[965,1262,690,717]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Pireneitega" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[965,1095,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">Pireneitega</emphasis>
Kishida, 1955
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhao, Z. &amp; Li, S. Q." pageId="1" pageNumber="358" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref9236" refString="Zhao, Z., &amp; Li, S. Q. (2017) Extinction vs. rapid radiation: the juxtaposed evolutionary histories of coelotine spiders support the Eocene - Oligocene orogenesis of the Tibetan plateau. Systematic Biology, 6, 1 - 24. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / sysbio / syx 042" type="journal article" year="2017">Zhao &amp; Li (2017)</bibRefCitation>
placed it as the sister group of 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang, 2002" authorityName="Wang" authorityYear="2002" box="[576,883,727,753]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Himalcoelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[576,738,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="358">Himalcoelotes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, X. P." box="[744,883,727,753]" pageId="1" pageNumber="358" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref8867" refString="Wang, X. P. (2002) A generic-level revision of the spider subfamily Coelotinae (Araneae, Amaurobiidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 269, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2002) 269 % 3 C 0001: AGLROT % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2002">Wang, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
